IBADAN – The immediate past ALGON Chairman, Oyo State, Prince Ayodeji Abass-Aleshinloye, has commiserated with Senator Teslim Folarin whose wife, Angela, passed away on Friday. In a statement released to journalists, Prince Aleshinloye said that it was heartbreaking to hear of the unexpected passing of Barrister Angela Folarin, noting that her death was a great loss not just to her family but to society at large. “Barrister (Mrs) Angela’s contribution to the society was laudable and worthy of commendation and urged her husband, children and other family members to be consoled by the legacies she left behind,” Aleshinloye said. Akpabio Urges Electorate To Re-elect Performing Officeholders Tanker Explosion: Soludo Commiserates With Victims “I learnt of the untimely passing of Barrister Angela Folarin, the wife of my brother, Senator Teslim Folarin. “It is indeed heartbreaking to lose a dear one, especially a wife of many years. “Although death is the way of all mortals and debt we must all pay, I am nonetheless consoled by the fact that Barrister Folarin lived a worthy and exemplary life. “My thoughts and prayers are with you (Senator Folarin). May Almighty Allah comfort you and the family at this moment. May He give you the strength and courage to bear it all.”